# Canvas Engine Rules

## ReactFlow Setup
- Use @xyflow/react v12 (not v11 — API is different)
- Wrap in <ReactFlowProvider> at the app level (not per-page)
- Always pass nodeTypes and edgeTypes as STATIC objects (defined outside component or useMemo)
- Never define nodeTypes/edgeTypes inline — causes re-render loops

## Performance Rules (CRITICAL)
- Wrap ALL custom node components in React.memo()
- Wrap ALL node event handlers in useCallback()
- Wrap defaultEdgeOptions and snapGrid in useMemo()
- Store selected node IDs separately in Zustand — NEVER derive from nodes array
- Use node.hidden = true for semantic zoom level switching (don't unmount)
- Limit visible nodes to current zoom level's semantic set
- NEVER use backdrop-filter: blur() on node components — tanks FPS at 100+ nodes
- Use CSS transform only (no opacity animations) for node transitions

## Semantic Zoom Implementation
Zoom levels map to what's rendered:
- viewport.zoom < 0.3 → Z0: Show ProjectClusterNode only (hide all phase/task nodes)
- 0.3 ≤ zoom < 0.7 → Z1: Show ProjectClusterNode + PhaseClusterNode (hide task nodes)
- 0.7 ≤ zoom < 1.5 → Z2: Show all nodes including TaskCardNode
- zoom ≥ 1.5 → Z3: TaskCardNode expands to show full detail

Implement via useViewport() hook + node.hidden toggling in a useEffect.
Do NOT use CSS zoom — use ReactFlow's built-in zoom system only.

## Node Types (locked)
- ProjectClusterNode: Outer container for a project (non-draggable position, resizable)
- PhaseClusterNode: Sub-container within a project
- TaskCardNode: Individual task card (the primary interactive element)
- MilestoneNode: Diamond-shaped milestone marker
- PersonAvatarNode: Floating workload avatar (workload layer only, hidden by default)

## Edge Types (locked)
- DependencyEdge: Standard FS dependency (bezier, animated when source is in-progress)
- BlockedEdge: Same as DependencyEdge but amber color + dashed
- CriticalPathEdge: Gold, 2px strokeWidth — rendered on top of all other edges
- CrossProjectEdge: Dashed gray — only visible at Z0/Z1

## Zustand Canvas Store (src/stores/canvas.store.ts)
Must contain:
- nodes: Node[] + edges: Edge[] (source of truth for ReactFlow)
- viewport: { x, y, zoom }
- selectedNodeId: string | null (NOT derived from nodes)
- activeLayer: 'default' | 'workload' | 'criticalPath'
- zoomLevel: 'Z0' | 'Z1' | 'Z2' | 'Z3'
- expandedProjects: Set<string>

## CPM Integration
- After any task mutation, call lib/cpm/compute.ts with the full task graph
- CPM result updates node data (isCriticalPath, slackTime, cascadeRisk)
- This triggers a shallow ReactFlow node update (not a full re-render)
- CPM runs client-side for instant feedback, server-side for persistence
